But this is my lucky tie.

13:02.460 --> 13:04.857
And anyone who knows me well
would know that.

13:04.917 --> 13:06.878
And just like I know
you only wear that sweater

13:06.886 --> 13:09.186
When you're planning on
eating pasta with red sauce.

13:09.254 --> 13:12.150
- Nice haircut.
- Let's level the playing field.

13:12.185 --> 13:15.403
How about the most we can spend
on each other's gifts is...

13:15.438 --> 13:16.618
zero dollars?

13:16.660 --> 13:19.227
- Really?
- You want to exchange creative gifts?

13:19.329 --> 13:20.562
Oh, well.

13:20.630 --> 13:22.380
You are the one that's
in trouble now, buddy,

13:22.415 --> 13:25.366
Because creativity to me
is just like...

13:25.435 --> 13:28.870
It's like a bird, like a friendly bird

13:28.938 --> 13:31.438
that embraces all...

13:31.506 --> 13:34.674
Ideas and just, like, shoots...

13:34.743 --> 13:36.643
Out of its eyes all kinds of beauty.

13:36.711 --> 13:39.312
Wow, Lemon, this is like
watching Hemingway write.

13:39.380 --> 13:40.646
Mark Hemingway.

13:40.714 --> 13:41.567
Yeah.

13:41.683 --> 13:43.115
Wait, why are you wearing
your lucky tie?

13:43.183 --> 13:45.884
I'm having dinner tonight with Nancy.
Alone.

13:45.952 --> 13:48.320
She changed her status to "weirdsies."

13:48.387 --> 13:50.523
What are your expectations here?
She's married.

13:50.591 --> 13:52.980
Uh, I don't know, Lemon.
Nancy's leaving tomorrow.

13:53.126 --> 13:54.661
Can't I just enjoy this while it lasts?

13:54.728 --> 13:57.330
That's what I said when that
hot dog vendor passed out,

13:57.397 --> 14:01.102
<i>But you made me go get help.</i>

14:03.638 --> 14:04.871
Hey!

14:04.938 --> 14:06.652
Did you hire this guy
to hide in my dressing room

14:06.687 --> 14:07.541
and punch me in the throat?

14:07.607 --> 14:10.910
- No.
- He's bigger than you said.

14:10.977 --> 14:12.311
May I still collect my kiss?

14:12.378 --> 14:14.882
Vattene!

14:14.949 --> 14:18.184
Why would you do that, Jenna?
I thought we were buddies.

14:18.252 --> 14:19.117
[chuckles]

14:19.221 --> 14:21.253
You don't fool me with your innocent act.

14:21.321 --> 14:23.520
First you force your way into my solo...

14:23.523 --> 14:24.726
I didn't force anything.

14:24.792 --> 14:26.260
Pete is the one that wanted
to take away your solo.

14:26.326 --> 14:27.706
What?
Why?

14:27.741 --> 14:30.429
He's mad that you don't chip in for
the cleaning lady's Christmas gifts.

14:30.497 --> 14:32.499
Well, I'm doing my own thing.

14:32.565 --> 14:36.002
I got them this.

14:36.069 --> 14:40.274
The program from this year's
Asian women in television awards.

14:40.810 --> 14:44.412
Julie Chen's energy drink,
Chenergize.

14:45.077 --> 14:46.214
A flipvideo.

14:46.282 --> 14:48.134
Wait, hang on, I didn't know
this was in here.

14:48.184 --> 14:49.918
Wow, you really get in
the Christmas spirit.

14:49.985 --> 14:51.853
[snaps fingers]
Oh, my God.

14:51.920 --> 14:53.421
I just got sarcasm.

14:53.488 --> 14:55.122
Fine.

14:55.190 --> 14:58.124
I'm terrible at Christmas
because I never had a nice one.

14:58.193 --> 15:00.579
Sometimes my mom would take us
to see Santa Claus,

15:00.614 --> 15:03.196
But that's just because she suspected
one of them was my deadbeat dad.

15:03.264 --> 15:06.599
So I'd have to get on every santa's lap
in the Bakersfield area and scream,

15:06.667 --> 15:08.701
"you oughta be ashamed
of yourself, Travis!"

15:08.768 --> 15:11.370
Oh, no, that's...
that sounds horrible.

15:11.437 --> 15:13.105
And then I'd sing carols
in the middle of Sears

15:13.172 --> 15:15.641
just to create a distraction
while my mom shoplifted.

15:15.709 --> 15:18.711
And those few minutes
when I was singing carols,

15:18.778 --> 15:21.147
that was the one part
of Christmas I liked.

15:21.214 --> 15:25.051
And now you've taken that
away from me.

15:28.755 --> 15:29.954
Well, that went well.

15:30.021 --> 15:31.122
[snaps fingers]

15:31.190 --> 15:33.291
Oh, yes.

15:35.597 --> 15:37.862
You're just a Kenny Rogers doll now.

15:41.235 --> 15:42.235
Something you wanna say?

15:42.301 --> 15:45.671
We wanna do secret santa!
Yay!

15:45.738 --> 15:49.476
Secret Santa has been cancelled
because I have lost my faith.

15:49.543 --> 15:51.750
But something's changed in us.

15:51.785 --> 15:53.145
It's... it's a Christmas miracle.

15:53.213 --> 15:54.814
That certainly proves God exists.

15:54.883 --> 15:59.219
If God existed, then he would punish you
for what you did to me.

15:59.254 --> 16:01.722
And yet here you are unpunished.

16:01.790 --> 16:06.093
Ergo, our actions have no consequences.

16:06.161 --> 16:07.628
So if you'll excuse me,

16:07.696 --> 16:10.565
I'm gonna go buy some guitar music.

16:15.137 --> 16:17.164
Hey, what was the name
of that abandoned factory

16:17.199 --> 16:19.275
where we used to go
shoot bb guns at rats?

16:19.342 --> 16:20.677
Wolford Cap and Gown.

16:20.777 --> 16:22.455
Of course.
Is that still there?

16:22.545 --> 16:25.347
No, they tore it down
and put up a big playground.

16:25.415 --> 16:28.450
- Oh, what a shame.
- Yeah.

16:28.519 --> 16:33.122
- So, uh, can I buy you a nightcap?
- Better not.

16:33.189 --> 16:35.525
We have an early train
back to Boston tomorrow.

16:35.592 --> 16:38.461
And you know how hard it is to get
teenagers out of bed in the mornin'.

16:38.529 --> 16:40.732
Yes, but not in the way
you're talking about.

16:40.799 --> 16:43.401
[both chuckle]

16:43.468 --> 16:44.769
It was great to see you, Jack.

16:44.837 --> 16:47.071
I'll, uh...
I'll hit ya on YouFace.

16:47.138 --> 16:49.341
But you gotta promise me
to finger tag me back.

16:49.408 --> 16:52.644
I'd like nothing more.

17:03.258 --> 17:05.925
[car horns honking]

17:06.707 --> 17:07.560
What is this?

17:07.628 --> 17:10.364
This is your zero dollars present.

17:10.431 --> 17:14.468
♪ doo doo-doo-doo,
doo-doo, my friend is Jack ♪

17:14.536 --> 17:17.238
♪ if you like his necktie,
pat him on the back ♪

17:17.305 --> 17:19.272
Nope. Never mind.
Not your present.

17:19.340 --> 17:22.076
Uh, no, please.
Don't go.

17:22.144 --> 17:27.049
Uh, I'm sorry that I wasn't even able to
feign interest in whatever that was.

17:27.115 --> 17:29.283
[uncorks bottle]

17:29.351 --> 17:30.584
Nancy left this morning.

17:30.653 --> 17:32.953
She'll be on the 12:10
out of Penn station.

17:33.618 --> 17:36.289
Do you ever wonder, Lemon,
what your life would be like

17:36.359 --> 17:38.560
if you had never left your hometown?

17:38.628 --> 17:39.200
Oh, of course.

17:39.395 --> 17:41.262
Have you not read my
terrible short story,

17:41.331 --> 17:43.532
<i>The two paths of Virginia apple?</i>

17:43.967 --> 17:47.462
I spent my whole life trying to erase
where I came from.

17:47.497 --> 17:49.504
But after these moments with Nancy,

17:49.572 --> 17:54.108
for the first time in my life,
I'm homesick.

17:54.175 --> 17:55.775
Well, you'll stay in touch, right?

17:55.843 --> 17:57.077
I don't know.

17:57.144 --> 18:00.279
Nancy's going back to her husband,
her life.

18:00.348 --> 18:02.117
I think this was just a moment in time

18:02.182 --> 18:05.084
and I just wish it had lasted
a little bit longer.

18:08.022 --> 18:10.059
Okay, well.

18:10.125 --> 18:14.028
I'm gonna go work on your real gift.

18:14.096 --> 18:17.265
You know what would go real nice
on that wall over there:

18:17.333 --> 18:19.267
A drawing of a frog.

18:19.335 --> 18:21.102
- No.
- No.

18:21.171 --> 18:22.273
[silently]
No.

18:23.297 --> 18:25.974
Back in five, four,

18:26.042 --> 18:29.277
Three, two...

18:29.345 --> 18:33.081
[piano music]

18:33.149 --> 18:35.082
♪ frosted window panes ♪

18:35.150 --> 18:37.319
♪ candles gleaming inside ♪

18:37.386 --> 18:41.755
♪ painted candy canes on the tree ♪

18:41.823 --> 18:44.359
[off key]
♪ santa's on his way ♪

18:44.426 --> 18:48.061
♪ he's filled his sleigh with things ♪

18:48.131 --> 18:50.731
♪ things for you and me ♪

18:50.799 --> 18:52.800
♪ it's that time of year ♪

18:52.867 --> 18:55.035
♪ when the world falls in love ♪

18:55.102 --> 18:58.905
♪ every song you hear seems to say ♪

18:58.973 --> 19:01.441
Both: ♪ Merry Christmas ♪

19:01.509 --> 19:07.348
♪ may your New Year's dreams come true ♪

19:07.416 --> 19:13.120
♪ ♪

19:13.189 --> 19:14.689
Hey, Jack.

19:14.756 --> 19:16.257
My train got cancelled.

19:16.325 --> 19:19.127
I spent all day at Penn station
trying to get out.

19:19.194 --> 19:22.131
Figured I should finally take the hint
and meet ya for that drink.

19:22.197 --> 19:26.068
Well, I'm glad you came back.

19:26.135 --> 19:29.571
And I figured I owed you a kiss good-bye.

19:29.639 --> 19:31.506
I mean, what's the big deal?

19:31.574 --> 19:33.174
We did it every night
in <i>Hey, Beantown.</i>

19:33.242 --> 19:36.944
We'll just do it high school style.

19:37.012 --> 19:39.480
No tongue.

19:48.924 --> 19:51.259
♪ and this song of mine ♪

19:51.327 --> 19:53.028
[off-key]
♪ in three-quarter time ♪

19:53.094 --> 19:55.861
♪ wishes you and yours ♪

19:55.930 --> 19:58.865
Both: ♪ the same thing too ♪

19:58.932 --> 20:03.470
Merry Christmas, Lemon.

20:07.141 --> 20:09.777
<i>The gender blind Crucible.</i>

20:09.843 --> 20:12.947
Framed in wood from the stage
of your high school theater.

20:13.013 --> 20:14.713
Jonathan had to drive
all over Pennsylvania

20:14.781 --> 20:17.217
and I did not reimburse him for gas.

20:17.284 --> 20:18.383
Zero dollars.

20:18.451 --> 20:20.352
Thank you, Jack.
That's amazing.

20:20.419 --> 20:21.954
And don't worry about my present.

20:22.022 --> 20:24.258
I already got the greatest Christmas gift
you could imagine.

20:24.324 --> 20:26.359
Nancy came back to say good-bye.

20:26.428 --> 20:27.728
Her train was cancelled.

20:27.794 --> 20:31.063
Because somebody called in
a bomb threat to Penn station?

20:31.131 --> 20:32.231
You're welcome.

20:32.299 --> 20:35.033
Merry Christmas.

20:38.138 --> 20:40.472
All right, which one of you are
Frank Rossitano and James Spurlock?

20:40.539 --> 20:41.673
- That's us.
- They are we.

20:41.740 --> 20:43.775
- You're under arrest.
- What did we do?

20:43.841 --> 20:47.277
Someone called in a bomb threat
from your phone this morning.

20:47.346 --> 20:49.114
I renounce Verdukianism!

20:49.180 --> 20:50.480
What's that mean?

20:50.548 --> 20:53.049
Are you Al Qaeda?
Come here, pal!

20:53.116 --> 20:54.450
[hollering]

20:54.517 --> 20:55.785
[wailing]

20:55.852 --> 20:58.554
[screaming]
Watch the head!

20:58.621 --> 21:01.555
My angry God is punishing them.

21:01.624 --> 21:03.757
It's a Christmas miracle.

21:03.825 --> 21:06.159
♪ and this song of mine ♪

21:06.227 --> 21:08.127
♪ in three-quarter time ♪

21:08.195 --> 21:10.662
Both: ♪ wishes you and yours ♪

21:10.732 --> 21:14.733
[in tune]
♪ the same thing too ♪

21:14.802 --> 21:19.672
Both: ♪ merry Christmas to you ♪

21:28.322 --> 21:30.590
- Are you Larry Wilcox?
- Yes, ma'am.

21:30.657 --> 21:33.383
This evening, you have permission
to call me officer John Baker.

21:34.027 --> 21:37.564
Oh, but, uh, no sex stuff
and no touching my gun.

21:37.631 --> 21:39.732
Of course, yeah.

21:39.799 --> 21:43.203
Merry Christmas, Lemon.

21:43.270 --> 21:45.370
Okay.

21:45.438 --> 21:46.473
Hee hee hee!

21:46.539 --> 21:48.774
Wait, how is this zero dollars?

21:48.841 --> 21:51.478
Well, he promised to get me
on <i>Dancing with the stars.</i>

21:51.545 --> 21:55.114
But that's on ABC.

21:55.182 --> 21:56.277
Donaghy!

